3. The union of all `S_n` is the entire space `Ω` (up to a null set)
4. The property `P` holds on the complement of the union of `S_n`.

In our case, the property `P` is `∀ ω, ∀ x, ∃ l, Tendsto (X · ω) (𝓝[<] x) (𝓝 l)`. The localizing sequence is given by `isLocalizingSequence_ae` in the previous problem.

